<P>
INDIAN BLOCKADES HALT RAILROAD TRAFFIC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Cross-Canadian rail traffic was stopped for a second day by two Indian 
blockades in northwestern Ontario. Spokesmen for the Long Lake Ojibwa band and 
the Pic Mobert Ojibwa band said they will not remove their blockades until 
Indian Affairs Minister Tom Siddon or his deputy minister meet them for 
face-to-face talks. Bernard Abraham of the Long Lake group said the Indians 
want their land expanded, "deplorable" housing conditions improved and services 
upgraded. 
</P>
</TEXT>
