<P>
GOVERNOR PLANS CUTS IN LOCAL AID 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Gov. L. Douglas Wilder said he plans to cut $333 million in local aid to help 
balance the state budget, and those reductions will hurt school budgets. 
</P>
<P>
Speaking to state Senate committees in Richmond, Va., Wilder detailed his plans 
to deal with a projected $1.4-billion deficit in the state's $26-billion 
1990-92 biennial budget. Wilder's budget director, Karen Washabau, said other 
cuts the governor has proposed in state agency spending could cause 400 to 
1,500 layoffs. But she said those figures were tentative until the governor 
decides on Sept. 14 what specific cuts he will order. 
</P>
</TEXT>
