<P>
NISEI WEEK IN LITTLE TOKYO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
This year marks the 50th anniversary of Nisei Week, a festival to honor the 
cultural heritage of the Nisei, who are second-generation Japanese-Americans. 
</P>
<P>
One of the highlights of the celebration will be a parade Sunday through Little 
Tokyo featuring dancing, music and 37 marching samurai warriors. It will be 
attended by Princess Sayako of Japan. Events, many of them free, will continue 
through Aug. 26. Here is a sampling: 
</P>
</TEXT>
