<HEADLINE>
<P>
FORCES BEHIND IMMIGRATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The commentary by Asencio and Torres reveals the hidden agenda behind the 
free-trade talks with Mexico. 
</P>
<P>
The authors confessed it is their "hope that fostering (economic) growth in 
migrant-sending countries (like Mexico) would eliminate the need to enforce our 
immigration laws." 
</P>
<P>
This call for open borders has been a frequent cry from voices on both sides of 
the border. For example, Mexico wants more than just free trade. President 
Carlos Salinas de Gortari has indicated he wants to see the "free movement of 
labor" as a part of any trade agreement. 
</P>
<P>
Likewise, many politicos in this country are also hoping to get more than a 
free trade agreement with Mexico. 
</P>
<P>
The trade talks with Mexico involve more than meets the eye. Many want an 
open-border agreement, and some even want to achieve a political harmonization 
with Mexico. American citizens should beware. 
</P>
<P>
ERICH PRATT 
</P>
<P>
Executive Director 
</P>
<P>
United States Border Control 
</P>
<P>
Springfield, Va. 
</P>
