<HEADLINE>
<P>
CONTROVERSY IS ONE THING, BUT GIVE FANS SOME GOLF 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Trying to watch golf on ABC during the PGA was futile. 
</P>
<P>
The most important aspect of this tournament to ABC was obviously the 
controversy about blacks not belonging to country clubs. I have never been so 
sick of a subject. They beat it to death Friday night instead of showing the 
tournament; they beat it to death Saturday and Sunday. It would be nice to be 
able to watch some of the tournament. 
</P>
<P>
JAMES ASHBY 
