<HEADLINE>
<P>
CONTROVERSY IS ONE THING, BUT GIVE FANS SOME GOLF 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In the Viewpoint letters Aug. 11, Sandy Cohen stated that the media had blown 
the Shoal Creek situation out of proportion and that a more urgent need was to 
" . . . educate young blacks so that they can get better jobs and economically 
have their own private clubs." 
</P>
<P>
Perhaps even more urgent is the need to educate whites, both young and old, so 
that there will be no more private clubs like Shoal Creek. 
</P>
<P>
WILLIAM M. HOMANN 
</P>
<P>
San Marcos 
</P>
