<HEADLINE>
<P>
BUSTER DOUGLAS JUST DOING WHAT WILL SELL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
So Mike Downey believes Buster Douglas is blowing his image (Aug. 8). 
</P>
<P>
Why? Because he is doing what every other athlete does, and that is to psych 
himself up by mouthing off, with expectations of generating interest and 
building the gate. 
</P>
<P>
As Muhammad Ali said, "If your opponent listened to all of your hype and 
rhetoric, you already have the edge going into the fight." 
</P>
<P>
I seriously doubt if we will have another "Ah was lucky," a la Joe Louis or 
Rocky Marciano. The name of the game today is hype. 
</P>
<P>
WILLIAM BROWN 
</P>
<P>
Carson 
</P>
