his family about 7:10 a.m., moments after they awoke to gunfire in the home in 
the 22300 block of South Harvard Avenue. 
</P>
<P>
Hinrichs said family members told police that they heard footsteps in the house 
just after the shooting but saw no intruder. They told police that the front 
door was open after the shooting. 
</P>
<P>
No motive for the killing has been established, Hinrichs said. 
