<HEADLINE>
<P>
7 KILLED IN GUN BATTLE WITH PHILIPPINE REBELS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
TACLOBAN, Philippines 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Communist rebels ambushed a police jeep in the central Philippines on Friday, 
killing a 13-year-old boy. Police fought back and killed six guerrillas, police 
officials said. 
</P>
<P>
Four police officers and two rebels were wounded in the 30-minute gun battle 
near Tacloban, 350 miles southeast of Manila. 
</P>
</TEXT>
