<HEADLINE>
<P>
GAS MASKS PUT BITE ON BEARDS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
JERUSALEM 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Israel's chief rabbi has asked religious Jews to carry scissors so they can 
remove their beards to accommodate gas masks if Iraq threatens Israel with 
chemical weapons. 
</P>
<P>
Rabbi Mordechai Eliahu ruled that Orthodox Jews need not follow a biblical ban 
on shaving beards -- if their lives are in danger. Under Jewish law, saving a 
life takes precedence over all other requirements. 
</P>
<P>
Some religious scholars believe the Bible meant for beards to distinguish Jews 
from non-Jews. But beards could interfere with the seal of the gas masks that 
Israel would issue to defend against an Iraqi poison gas attack. 
</P>
</TEXT>
