<P>
DRIVER DIES IN TRUCK FIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
PORTER, Me. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A truck hauling 9,000 gallons of gasoline overturned and exploded Friday, 
killing the driver and igniting a fire so intense that firefighters were 
blistered through their protective clothing, authorities said. The accident 
occurred in an unpopulated area near this southwestern Maine town. 
