<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Both sides in the dispute that threatened to cancel a Soviet-NHL exhibition 
series claimed victory after the Soviet Ice Hockey Federation decided to go 
ahead with a tour of NHL cities this winter. 
</P>
<P>
Federation President Leonid Kravchenko said in Moscow that the Soviets had 
agreed to the full schedule of 29 exhibitions. Kravchenko said the decision was 
made after the NHL had "promised to give legal guarantees that there will be no 
future situations where 'stealing' of our players will occur." 
</P>
<P>
However, Alan Eagleson, head of the NHL Players' Assn., said the league could 
give no such assurances. 
</P>
</TEXT>
