The leader of the Texas House of Representatives vowed to use his political 
power to keep Texas and Texas A&amp;M from leaving the Southwest Conference, 
defections other schools say would destroy the 76-year-old league. 
</P>
<P>
House Speaker Gib Lewis (D-Ft. Worth) said he would go so far as to reduce 
legislative appropriations to the two public universities if they tried to 
leave. 
