</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FundAmerica Files for Bankruptcy Protection: The Irvine-based buying club 
accused of being a pyramid scheme asked the court to name an independent 
examiner to investigate allegations against it. 
</P>
<P>
The company is besieged by regulators in Florida and other states and is the 
subject of a $150-million class-action suit in San Francisco. Its bankruptcy 
filing in Santa Ana, which was expected, listed assets of $17.5 million and 
liabilities of $14.5 million. FundAmerica has about 100,000 members. 
</P>
