Soviets Propose Foreign Ownership: The government has submitted a bill to 
parliament that would allow foreign companies to become sole owners of new 
enterprises, Prime Minister Nikolai Ryzhkov said. It would be the first time in 
at least 60 years that foreigners have been allowed to wholly own businesses 
operating in the Soviet Union. 
