</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Reports of Cuts at Sears: Sears, Roebuck &amp; Co. plans to eliminate thousands 
of jobs in the coming months to help cut costs and improve profits, according 
to a Wall Street Journal story. The Chicago-based retailer would not confirm 
the report. The move, involving administrative and retail employees, is 
expected to result in annual savings of more than $100 million, the Journal 
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
SEARS ROEBUCK AND CO; DEPARTMENT STORES -- LAYOFFS 
</P>
