ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: GARDEN GROVE; 
</P>
<P>
BOY, 4, DIES AFTER BEING STRUCK BY CAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 4-year-old boy died Friday morning after being struck by a car in Garden 
Grove, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Jose Roberto Valladares died after being hospitalized overnight in the 
pediatric intensive-care unit at UCI Medical Center in Orange, hospital 
spokeswoman Fran Tardiff said. 
</P>
<P>
Jose was playing in the front yard of his home in the 12000 block of Buaro 
Street at 5:30 p.m. Thursday when he suddenly dashed out into the street, 
Garden Grove Police Lt. Kenneth Adair said. 
</P>
<P>
"The child ran out from between two parked cars," Adair said. "Nobody seems to 
know why the kid ran into the street." 
</P>
<P>
Sasha Brooks, 19, of Garden Grove, could not stop her 1985 Mitsubishi in time 
to avoid the child. Jose suffered massive head injuries and was rushed to the 
hospital. The driver was not cited in the accident, Adair said. 
</P>
