EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Care Enterprises Inc., a Tustin-based nursing-facility company, posted a net 
loss of $22,000 for the second quarter, compared to a net loss of $455,000 for 
last year's second quarter. Revenue dropped 16% to $57.3 million from $68.4 
million. The company attributed the decline to fewer Medicare patients because 
of the repeal of the Medicare Catastrophic Coverage Act and to fewer nursing 
facilities operated during the second quarter of 1990. 
