<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFCASE: REAL ESTATE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Michael Flagg Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Big-Time Groundbreaking: There aren't many groundbreakings that draw big-time 
developers Arthur B. Birtcher, co-chairman of Laguna Niguel's Birtcher; Anthony 
R. Moiso, president of the huge land-owning Santa Margarita Co., and hamburger 
magnate Carl N. Karcher. 
</P>
<P>
Those people and more, however, showed up this week for the groundbreaking of 
an extension of the Heart of Jesus Retreat Center in Santa Ana. 
</P>
<P>
The center, run by the Sisters of the Society Devoted to the Sacred Heart, is 
the only one in Southern California that concentrates on developing the faith 
of Roman Catholic children. 
</P>
<P>
The center, at 2927 S. Greenville St. near South Coast Plaza, has been open 
since 1979. The expansion will add 25,000 square feet, including an assembly 
room, dining hall, playing field and living space for the sisters. They hope 
for up to 29,000 visitors a year when the $3.8-million expansion is finished. 
</P>
<P>
Birtcher, Moiso and other local heavy hitters -- including County Supervisor 
Thomas F. Riley and home-builders Al and Jim Baldwin -- raised $4.3 million for 
the construction and for the sisters' work. Birtcher's construction company is 
general contractor on the project. 
</P>
</TEXT>
